<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF3E6A81FA8D9067176FBC71" pageId="197" pageNumber="959" type="description">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF3E6A81FA8D9067176FBC71" blockId="197.[1391,2599,1548,2254]" pageId="197" pageNumber="959">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF3E6A81FA8D9067186CBD65" bold="true" box="[1393,1644,1598,1623]" pageId="197" pageNumber="959">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body ¢.40- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3E6A81F891906719C6BD65" box="[1901,1990,1598,1623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="197" pageNumber="959" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
, tail ¢.38: 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3E6A81F7AB906716AEBD65" box="[2135,2222,1598,1623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="197" pageNumber="959" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
, ear c.15- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3E6A81F6C190671798BD65" box="[2365,2456,1598,1623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="197" pageNumber="959" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
, hindfoot c.7- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3E6A81FA5D90051BF4BD4F" box="[1441,1524,1628,1661]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="197" pageNumber="959" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
, forearm c.35- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF3E6A81F9479005190BBD4F" box="[1723,1803,1628,1661]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="197" pageNumber="959" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
(type specimen). Dorsal pelage is blackish, ventral pelage is lighter. Membranes, ears, and limbs are dark brown. Earis long, with a deeply concave upper outer margin, being strongly and abruptly convex on lower two-thirds; tragus is straight and subacutely pointed at tip, with basal lobe on posterior margin. Wings attach at base offirst toe; feet are small and slender. Last vertebrae oftail extends past margin of uropatagium. P° and P, are small and within their respective tooth rows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
